    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add the<strong> butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until softened and starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the butternut squash is cooking, heat a large pot over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, stirring occasionally, until golden and crisp</p><p>Once crisp, transfer the bacon lardons to kitchen paper and reserve the pot</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 650ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat, once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and <strong>chopped potato</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 10-12 min or until the potato is beginning to break down</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces and add them to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>pine kernel & seed mix</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until golden \u2013 these are your <strong>chilli-cheese croutons</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potato has started to break down, add the<strong> roasted butternut squash cubes</strong> to the pot and blend with a<strong> (stick) blender</strong> until a smooth soup remains</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if your soup is looking a little thick!</p><p>Stir through your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche </strong>and taste for seasoning, adding a little more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy butternut squash soup</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-butternut-squash-and-bacon-soup-with-chilli-cheese-croutons/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy butternut squash soup</strong> in bowls and top with the <strong>crispy bacon lardons</strong> and <strong>chilli-cheese croutons</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
